---
globs: apps/web/lib/schema.ts, apps/web/lib/db.ts, apps/worker/worker/db.py, **/migrations/**, **/*.sql
alwaysApply: false
---

The MVP database is SQLite located at:

data/app.db

The web app uses Drizzle.
The Python worker uses SQLAlchemy.
Both layers must represent the same schema.

When changing schema:
- Update Drizzle schema in apps/web/lib/schema.ts.
- Update SQLAlchemy models in apps/worker/worker/db.py.
- Keep table names and column names consistent across TypeScript and Python.
- Update migrations or initialization logic if present.
- Do not update only one side.

Core tables should include:
- projects
- jobs
- transcripts
- transcript_words or equivalent word timestamp storage
- chat_messages or parsed chat event storage
- highlights
- clips
- accounts
- publishing_jobs or publishing-related job records if needed

Recommended project fields:
- id
- source_url
- source_platform
- title
- status
- source_video_path
- source_audio_path
- created_at
- updated_at

Recommended job fields:
- id
- project_id
- type
- status
- progress
- message
- error
- attempts
- run_after
- started_at
- finished_at
- created_at
- updated_at

Allowed job types:
- ingest
- transcribe
- analyze
- render
- publish

Recommended job statuses:
- queued
- running
- succeeded
- failed
- canceled

Timestamp rules:
- Store media timestamps consistently.
- Prefer milliseconds for internal clip/highlight boundaries.
- Convert to human-readable time only in UI.
- Transcript words should preserve precise start/end timestamps.

Media storage rules:
- Store file paths in SQLite.
- Store actual media files under data/videos/{project_id}/.
- Do not store binary video/audio/image files in SQLite.

Data integrity:
- Use foreign keys where possible.
- Jobs should reference projects.
- Highlights should reference projects.
- Clips should reference projects and optionally source highlights.
- Accounts should reference users if auth is added.
- Avoid destructive schema changes without a migration plan.
